<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,501,526]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length of male 
<quantity box="[563,716,501,525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.245" metricValueMax="4.61" metricValueMin="3.88" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="4.245" valueMax="4.61" valueMin="3.88">3.88–4.61 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number box="[823,875,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.34">4.34</number>
, n = 
<number box="[930,960,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.0">15</number>
), and female 
<quantity box="[1112,1251,501,525]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.395" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.99" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="4.395" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.99">3.99–4.8 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number box="[1358,1410,501,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.62">4.62</number>
, n = 
<number box="[173,189,537,561]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
). Very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[381,533,537,561]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[381,533,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but males can be easily distinguished from that species by the presence of a dorsal hair pencil in the hind wing discal cell. In males and females, postmedial border of dorsal forewing orange area less jagged than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[364,516,609,633]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[364,516,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Dorsal hind wing orange area usually smaller than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1125,1277,609,633]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[1125,1277,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. General ventral coloration more vivid than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[529,681,645,669]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[529,681,645,669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fresh specimens of both species were compared), making the ventral forewing brown submarginal band darker and better defined. Females are similar to, and difficult to separate from, those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[314,466,717,741]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[314,466,717,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Female ventral forewing brown submarginal band usually solid color, without the ripple pattern usually visible in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[475,627,753,777]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[475,627,753,777]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,314,789,814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Both the male and female genitalia are similar in size those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1035,1188,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[1035,1188,789,813]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male specimens (six dissections) varied in the width of the distal half of the valva, and also the number of subterminal spines at the dorsal edge (
<figureCitation box="[264,335,861,885]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[320,335,861,885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
E). The ventral outline of the valva in lateral view was consistent across specimens (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1400,861,885]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1400,861,885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Female sterigma with long lateral arms, main plate short and with a shorter midline lobe than 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1208,1314,897,921]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1314,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(three dissections). Corpus bursa oval shaped, with paired signa, and constricted at the meeting point with the narrow ductus bursa (
<figureCitation box="[227,294,969,993]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[279,294,969,993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
