<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,500,1077,1102]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Variation and subspecies.</emphasis>
The local and geographical color variation within 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1068,1161,1077,1101]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[1068,1161,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gave rise to the description of several subspecies and forms, and three valid subspecies are currently recognized (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Casagrande" box="[1224,1424,1113,1137]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Casagrande, M. M. (2004) Brassolini. p. 201 - 205. In: J. B. Heppner (ed.). Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A Checklist (ed. by G. Lamas). Association of Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific publishers, Gainesville. 439 p." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Casagrande 
<number box="[1363,1424,1113,1137]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): nominal 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[250,414,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis box="[250,414,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[429,479,1149,1173]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry box="[587,659,1149,1173]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[679,891,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="didymaon">
<emphasis box="[679,891,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea didymaon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[907,981,1149,1173]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fruhstorfer, 1907" authorityName="Fruhstorfer" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="praegrandis">
<emphasis box="[1048,1287,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea praegrandis</emphasis>
(Fruhstorfer, 
<number box="[151,208,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1907.0">1907</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[231,342,1185,1209]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
). The account for 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[544,637,1185,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[544,637,1185,1209]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fruhstorfer" box="[673,881,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number box="[814,872,1185,1209]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
is detailed and includes comments on 
<typeStatus box="[1314,1362,1186,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
specimens, and from that work it seems that the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[891,984,1221,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[891,984,1221,1245]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Hübner (
<number box="[1126,1184,1221,1245]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1821.0">1821</number>
) corresponds to a dorsally pale-orange colored specimen in which the delimitation between the dorsal forewing brown edge and orange base is approximately straight. This is the phenotype illustrated by D’Abrera (
<number box="[1036,1094,1293,1317]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1987.0">1987</number>
) and 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1221,1293,1317]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1211,1221,1293,1317]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K (Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro), and according to our samples it seems to be a less common phenotype than that in 
<figureCitation box="[1342,1409,1329,1353]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1409,1329,1353]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E. Although wing color and shape differences between 
<figureCitation box="[748,810,1365,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[800,810,1365,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K and 
<number box="[891,901,1365,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
E seem extreme, we have examined specimens with intermediate phenotypes from several locations including Nova Friburgo itself, and also Serra do Caraça (Minas Gerais), and São Paulo, and there are no obvious differences between male genitalia of these forms. From this we conclude that, as currently understood, 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[683,847,1473,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis box="[683,847,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a broad range of color variation, and subspecific definition within 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[409,504,1509,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[409,504,1509,1533]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore problematic. Although one specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1146,1250,1510,1534]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(Caazapá, P. N. Caaguazú) examined from a photograph matches the defining characters given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fruhstorfer" box="[1115,1326,1545,1569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number box="[1259,1318,1545,1569]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="praegrandis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. b. praegrandis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we found that such characters fit within the range of variation observed for 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1164,1329,1581,1605]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="batea">
<emphasis box="[1164,1329,1581,1605]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1367,1436,1581,1605]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(photographs of a Paraguayan specimen were provided by S. Rios, specimen from the Museo Nacional de Historia Natural del 
<collectingCountry box="[287,391,1654,1678]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
collection). Therefore, the status of this subspecies should be verified by examination of a series of specimens. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fruhstorfer" box="[383,591,1689,1713]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number box="[524,582,1689,1713]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that the width of the dorsal forewing dark brown area is narrowest at the northern part of the species distribution, progressively becoming broader towards southern localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1368,1437,1725,1749]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(and probably 
<collectingCountry box="[313,416,1761,1785]" name="Uruguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
). We confirmed his assessment, and southern specimens with little or no orange color distal from the dorsal forewing discal cell correspond to the described 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[884,1097,1797,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="batea" subSpecies="didymaon">
<emphasis box="[884,1097,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea didymaon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1114,1177,1797,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1177,1797,1821]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H and I). Nonetheless, we feel that the local and clinal variation in color pattern in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[844,939,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[844,939,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
calls the recognition of discrete subspecies into question.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,501,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,464,1905,1930]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Natural history notes.</emphasis>
The early stages of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[706,802,1905,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[706,802,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been described. André Freitas (pers. comm.) observed females of this species ovipositing on an unidentified grass, and notes that adults can be locally common on forest edges bordered by wet to flooded grassland in higher altitude localities. Reported host plants include 
<taxonomicName box="[151,274,2013,2037]" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Gramineae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[328,445,2014,2038]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Beccaloni" box="[504,746,2013,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Beccaloni, G. W., Viloria, A. L., Hall, S. K. &amp; Robinson, G. S. (2008) Catalogue of the hostplants of the Neotropical butterflies. Natural History Museum, London, 536 pp." type="book" year="2008">
Beccaloni 
<emphasis box="[622,678,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[685,746,2013,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
